RP TITLE

An RP title is a short cosmetic roleplay title shown before your
character's name (for example: Warlord Thurtea) anywhere your name
is displayed to others.

There is no command to set your own title. RP-Wizards grant titles
in recognition of roleplay; ask one in game if you feel you have
earned one. Titles are 2 to 20 characters, cosmetic only, and may
be revoked.

Staff commands:
  grant title <player> <title>     Award a title
  revoke title <player>            Remove a title

SEE ALSO: names, position, score
